Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of deep learning technologies, specifically word embeddings, to solve verbal comprehension questions in IQ tests. This falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as it specifically deals with NLP. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely categories as they cover the use of AI and ML technologies. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as it covers the use of neural networks, which are a key component of deep learning. Finally, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a less likely category, but it could be relevant as the paper discusses the challenges of solving IQ test questions using existing technologies.
